<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1438,1579,1748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,1579,1604]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[313,404,1580,1604]" name="Albania" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Albania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[417,491,1580,1604]" name="Russia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Russia</collectingCountry>
(south of the European part), 
<collectingCountry box="[840,904,1580,1604]" name="Spain" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, D. S. &amp; van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K." box="[920,1088,1580,1604]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref52118" refString="Yu, D. S., van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K. (2005) World Ichneumonoidea 2004. Taxonomy, Biology, Morphology and Distribution. CD / DVD. Taxapad, Vancouver, Canada. www. taxapad. com." type="book" year="2005">
Yu 
<emphasis box="[961,1012,1580,1604]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al</emphasis>
. 2005
</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<collectingCountry box="[1158,1229,1580,1604]" name="Serbia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Serbia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Belokobylskij, S. A. &amp; Zikic, V." pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="65 - 71" refId="ref47695" refString="Belokobylskij, S. A. &amp; Zikic, V. (2009) New data on cyclostome braconid subfamilies Doryctinae, Exothecinae, Rogadinae and Braconinae (Hymenoptera: Braconidae) of Serbia and neighbouring territories. Acta Entomologica Serbica, 143 (1), 65 - 71." type="journal article" year="2009">Belokobylskij &amp; Zikic 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1438,1579,1748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1652,1676]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is widely distributed but infrequently collected and occurs along the southern part of Europe from 
<collectingCountry box="[300,364,1687,1711]" name="Spain" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Spain</collectingCountry>
to the North Caucasus. 
<bibRefCitation author="Yu, D. S. &amp; van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K." box="[634,810,1687,1712]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref52118" refString="Yu, D. S., van Achterberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K. (2005) World Ichneumonoidea 2004. Taxonomy, Biology, Morphology and Distribution. CD / DVD. Taxapad, Vancouver, Canada. www. taxapad. com." type="book" year="2005">
Yu 
<emphasis box="[672,721,1688,1712]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">et al</emphasis>
. (2005)
</bibRefCitation>
listed it as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wesmael" authorityName="Wesmael" box="[1114,1434,1687,1712]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Spathius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pedestris">
<emphasis box="[1114,1319,1688,1712]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Spathius pedestris</emphasis>
Wesmael
</taxonomicName>
; we follow 
<bibRefCitation author="Belokobylskij, S. A." box="[270,509,1724,1748]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="347 - 488" refId="ref47154" refString="Belokobylskij, S. A. (2003) The species of the genus Spathius Nees, 1818 (Hymenoptera: Braconidae: Doryctinae) not included in the monograph by Nixon (1943). Annales Zoologici, 53 (3), 347 - 488." type="journal article" year="2003">Belokobylskij (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and recognize it as a species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
